jobs_results.title: iOS Developer
jobs_results.description:
ABOUT US

Hey there! Before we dive into the job details, let's give you a quick rundown of our company.

November Five is the go-to digital partner for customer experience leaders like Coca-Cola, Spotify, Telenet, Le Pain Quotidien, Mediahuis or KBC Bank. We don't shy away from a challenge. We pick projects where we can make a real difference and deliver digital products driving strong customer experience.

We prioritize impact over volume and foster a culture of ownership. At November Five, everyone leaves their mark. To get the best out of ourselves, we work from our office or remotely and invite others over to our collaboration hub for some inspiration. We're all about providing the best solutions, not just being present.

With a team of 70+ experts based in Antwerp, we've been on a digital adventure since 2008 and excited for what's to come!

ABOUT THE JOB

Are you ready to take your iOS development skills to the next level? Join November Five and lead the way in building and delivering cutting-edge mobile applications. This is your opportunity to make a real impact on a widely used application and to work closely with the client as a valued partner. You will work with the latest tools in iOS development like SwiftUI and Swift concurrency and join a team where meaningful contributions are made and your ideas are heard.

IF YOU JOIN US, YOU WILL:
‚Ä¢ Build powerful and performant apps by turning product requirements and UI designs into high-quality, pixel-perfect implementations
‚Ä¢ Consistently develop and improve functionalities, while optimizing for the best user experience
‚Ä¢ Keep up-to-date with the fast-evolving landscape of technologies and innovations, sharing your knowledge and expertise with your teammates

KEEP READING IF YOU...
‚Ä¢ Have experience building iOS applications with Swift
‚Ä¢ Master the art of coding: your code is clean and understandable, and you're proud of it!
‚Ä¢ Have a genuine interest or experience with other technologies, like Android, React (Native) or Serverless
‚Ä¢ Have experience with SwiftUI or scrum - that's a big plus!

FIVE REASONS TO APPLY RIGHT NOW
‚Ä¢ Aim for impact: we work towards meaningful impact on the digital experience of millions by building products for clients like Spotify, Coca-Cola, Telenet, VRT or Brussels Airport.
‚Ä¢ Continue to grow: define your own career path at N5 with our support. Meet with your Product Manager or Director for regular check-ins or lead an initiative during our bi-weekly meetups to learn a new skill. The sky's the limit at N5.
‚Ä¢ Unite in a cooperative spirit: thrive in close-knit teams - or squads as we call them - and mingle with like-minded peers both at work or during our after-hour activities.
‚Ä¢ Find your balance: with flexible hours and a hybrid work policy that allows you to choose your work location.
‚Ä¢ Enjoy a fully optimized salary package: including - depending on your role & expertise - a company car, pension plan, top notch health & well-being insurance, hospitalisation insurance, MacBook, smartphone with subscription, net expenses, meal vouchers, yearly bonus and 32 holidays.

jobs_results.title: Lead Developer Mobile Apps (iOS / Android) for Digital Health - Consulting
jobs_results.description:
At EY, you‚Äôll have the chance to build a career as unique as you are, with the global scale, support, inclusive culture and technology to become the best version of you. And we‚Äôre counting on your unique voice and perspective to help EY become even better, too. Join us and build an exceptional experience for yourself, and a better working world for all.

You will be part of EY‚Äôs EMEIA-based Digital Health Excellence Center (DHEC). Our mission is to improve health outcomes and patient experiences. As the DHEC, we bring our expert knowledge and delivery power to industry-leading healthcare providers in collaboration with the local firms.

The opportunity

As a senior developer, you will work alongside a team of international experts in technology, business and the healthcare industry. The end-to-end development and implementation of mobile apps is at the core of the DHEC, with you we want to further strengthen our technical expertise.

Your key responsibilities

As a senior developer, you are responsible for the development and implementation of innovative mobile software solutions for our healthcare clients. In your role, you will collaborate with clinical teams, administrators, and other healthcare professionals to prioritize and address health-specific software needs.

As technical expert, you work together with the development team in the creation of customer journey and user stories, you coordinate with UI/UX designers, and you collaborate with the software architects to implement functionality that is suitable for specific client needs. Additionally, you will be responsible for near- and off-shore technical teams, vendors, and external partners to ensure our products are consistent and reliable, as well as provide training and support in business development.

Skills and attributes for success
‚Ä¢ Strong written and verbal communication, presentation, client service and technical writing skills for both technical and business audiences.
‚Ä¢ Fluency in English and Proficiency in the local language of your country of residence is required.
‚Ä¢ Knowledge of additional languages will be appreciated.
‚Ä¢ Strong analytical, problem solving and critical thinking skills.
‚Ä¢ Ability to work under tight timelines for multiple project deliveries in parallel.
‚Ä¢ Ability/flexibility to travel.

To qualify for the role, you must have
‚Ä¢ Bachelor‚Äôs degree in informatics, Mathematics, (Software) Engineering or other related field with strong IT focus. Master's or further certification are advantageous.
‚Ä¢ Minimum of 2 years of working experience in a healthcare context and particular focus on implementing custom applications on mobile operating systems.
‚Ä¢ Deep understanding of development in iOS and Android using e.g. Swift, SwiftUI, Kotlin, and Jetpack Compose. Basic understanding of both operating systems is a prerequisite.
‚Ä¢ Expert knowledge of software architecture on all levels, i.e. network, infrastructure, security, persistence, application, and frontend.
‚Ä¢ Proven work experience in driving international development teams and managing different stakeholder groups, e.g. project managers, Scrum masters, product owners, business analysts, developers, and infrastructure and security architects.
‚Ä¢ Deep understanding of programming patterns (e.g. MVC, MVVM), tools, and frameworks for development (e.g. Declarative UI, Angular, Xamarin, React).

Ideally, you‚Äôll also have
‚Ä¢ A reliable network in the healthcare industry and a consulting track record.
‚Ä¢ A good overview of industry technology trends and emerging technologies, understand how they apply to our healthcare clients and can drive their adoption into our projects.
‚Ä¢ A solid understanding of health-specific interoperability formats, e.g. HL7/FHIR, SNOMED, OMOP, openEHR.
‚Ä¢ A good knowledge of system integration in medical system landscapes between software products of various clinical domains, e.g. Electronic Medical Records (EMR), Clinical Information Systems (CIS), Clinical Data Repositories (CDR), Laboratory Information Management Systems (LIMS), communication servers and interoperability platforms.

What we look for

We are looking for an experienced Senior Developer with strong technical skills and a proven track record working in a healthcare context.

What working at EY offers

As part of this role, you'll work in a highly integrated, global team with the opportunity and tools to grow, develop and drive your career forward. Here, you can combine global opportunity with flexible working. The EY benefits package goes above and beyond too, focusing on your physical, emotional, financial and social well-being. Your recruiter can talk to you about the benefits available in your country.

Here‚Äôs a snapshot of what we offer:
‚Ä¢ Continuous learning: You‚Äôll develop the mindset and skills to navigate whatever comes next.
‚Ä¢ Success as defined by you: We‚Äôll provide the tools and flexibility, so you can make a meaningful impact, your way.
‚Ä¢ Transformative leadership: We‚Äôll give you the insights, coaching and confidence to be the leader the world needs.
‚Ä¢ Diverse and inclusive culture: You‚Äôll be embraced for who you are and empowered to use your voice to help others find theirs.

About EY

If you can confidently demonstrate that you meet the criteria above, please contact us as soon as possible.

EY | Building a better working world

EY exists to build a better working world, helping to create long-term value for clients, people and society and build trust in the capital markets.

Enabled by data and technology, diverse EY teams in over 150 countries provide trust through assurance and help clients grow, transform and operate.

Working across assurance, consulting, law, strategy, tax and transactions, EY teams ask better questions to find new answers for the complex issues facing our world today.

jobs_results.description:
üöÄ What's the position?

This is a Full-time Senior iOS Developer position at Neybox for talented individuals who want to work on cutting-edge applications that positively impact the well-being of individuals worldwide.

üí´ What will I be working on?

You'll be working on our two apps: Pillow, a sleep-tracking app, and Today, which is a quantified-self wellness app.

Both apps have won an Editors' Choice distinction and have been featured multiple times in press and media. They have millions of users worldwide and a great roadmap ahead.

üßë‚Äçüíª What will be my role and responsibilities?

As a senior developer you will be responsible for
‚Ä¢ Building new features
‚Ä¢ Fixing bugs
‚Ä¢ Maintaining the existing codebase

‚Ä¢ Making sure the documentation of the project is accurate and helpful

‚Ä¢ ‚ö†Ô∏èThis is a position that requires a commitment of 40 hours per week. This is not a part-time position.

üõ†Ô∏è What's the tech stack?

In a nutshell:

Both our apps are written in Swift (MVVM and MVC).

The UI is written in SwiftUI and UIKit.

We write Unit Tests; the code is clean and well-documented.

We make extensive use of various frameworks and machine learning.

Both apps are available for iOS only.

üåç Can I work remotely?

Of course! Our team is 100% remote. We have flexible working hours, but a good overlap between our time zones is required.

üôå What is it like working at Neybox?

Our team is small by design (6-8 people). However, we work closely together every day (Mon-Fri). For coordination, we use Slack and Jira and keep meetings at a minimum.

There's no middle management to get in the way, and we encourage new ideas and close collaboration.

üíº What are the requirements?
‚Ä¢ 4+ years of iOS development experience in Swift

Just hit "Apply" button below!
